The first person to whom my hostess introduced me--with a subduedfanfare of social clarion--was the "English" cousin with whom Louise hadbeen staying in Devonshire, Lady Morgain, "daughter of our former Ambassadorand widow of the Oxford medievalist"--shadowy figures on a briefly litscreen. She was a rather deaf and decidedly dotty witch in her middlefifties, comically coiffured and dowdily dressed, and she and her be